b'[<p><i><b>UFC: Fight for the Troops 3</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 31</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on November 6, 2013, at <a href="/wiki/Fort_Campbell" title="Fort Campbell">Fort Campbell</a> in <a href="/wiki/Fort_Campbell_North,_Kentucky" title="Fort Campbell North, Kentucky">Fort Campbell, Kentucky</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Machida/Kennedy_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-Machida/Kennedy-2">[2]</a></sup> The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Fox_Sports_1" title="Fox Sports 1">Fox Sports 1</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was the fourth that <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a> hosted in cooperation with a US military base, following <a href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night:_Sanchez_vs._Riggs" title="UFC Fight Night: Sanchez vs. Riggs">UFC Fight Night: Sanchez vs. Riggs</a> in 2006, <a href="/wiki/UFC:_Fight_for_the_Troops" title="UFC: Fight for the Troops">UFC: Fight for the Troops</a> in 2008 and <a href="/wiki/UFC:_Fight_for_the_Troops_2" title="UFC: Fight for the Troops 2">UFC: Fight for the Troops 2</a> in 2011.  Featured on the card were several <a href="/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces" title="United States Armed Forces">United States Armed Forces</a> military veterans including <a href="/wiki/Tim_Kennedy_(fighter)" title="Tim Kennedy (fighter)">Tim Kennedy</a>, <a href="/wiki/Liz_Carmouche" title="Liz Carmouche">Liz Carmouche</a>, <a href="/wiki/Colton_Smith" title="Colton Smith">Colton Smith</a> and <a href="/wiki/Neil_Magny" title="Neil Magny">Neil Magny</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A bout between <a href="/wiki/George_Roop" title="George Roop">George Roop</a> and <a href="/wiki/Francisco_Rivera_(fighter)" title="Francisco Rivera (fighter)">Francisco Rivera</a>, previously linked to <a href="/wiki/UFC_166" title="UFC 166">UFC 166</a> was moved to this event to bolster the card.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Nik_Lentz" title="Nik Lentz">Nik Lentz</a> was briefly scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Dennis_Bermudez" title="Dennis Bermudez">Dennis Bermudez</a> at the event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>  However, Lentz was pulled from the pairing with Bermudez in favor of a bout with <a href="/wiki/Chad_Mendes" title="Chad Mendes">Chad Mendes</a> on December 14, 2013 at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_on_Fox_9" title="UFC on Fox 9">UFC on Fox 9</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup>  Bermudez then faced <a href="/wiki/Steven_Siler" title="Steven Siler">Steven Siler</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Derek_Brunson" title="Derek Brunson">Derek Brunson</a> was originally scheduled to face <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Antonio_Braga_Neto" title="Antonio Braga Neto">Antonio Braga Neto</a> on this card.  However, Neto withdrew due to an injury and was replaced by UFC newcomer Brian Houston.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Tim_Kennedy_(fighter)" title="Tim Kennedy (fighter)">Tim Kennedy</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Lyoto_Machida" title="Lyoto Machida">Lyoto Machida</a> in the event headliner.  However, Machida was pulled from the bout in favor of a matchup with <a href="/wiki/Mark_Mu%C3%B1oz" title="Mark Mu\xc3\xb1oz">Mark Mu\xc3\xb1oz</a> on October 26, 2013 at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night_30" title="UFC Fight Night 30">UFC Fight Night 30</a>, after Mu\xc3\xb1oz\'s original opponent, <a href="/wiki/Michael_Bisping" title="Michael Bisping">Michael Bisping</a> was forced out of their bout with an injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup> Kennedy instead faced <a href="/wiki/Rafael_Natal" title="Rafael Natal">Rafael Natal</a> in the event headliner.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-15"><a href="#cite_note-15">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>]'